59static inline bool isCSSWideKeyword(CSSValueID id)
60{
61 return id == CSSValueInitial || id == CSSValueInherit || id == CSSValueUnset || id == CSSValueRevert || id == CSSValueDefault;
62}
63
64bool consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
65{
66 CSSParserToken value = range.peek();
67 if (value.type() != CommaToken)
68 return false;
69 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
70 return true;
71}
72
73bool consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
74{
75 CSSParserToken value = range.peek();
76 if (value.type() != DelimiterToken || value.delimiter() != '/')
77 return false;
78 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
79 return true;
80}
81
82CSSParserTokenRange consumeFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
83{
84 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == FunctionToken);
85 CSSParserTokenRange contents = range.consumeBlock();
86 range.consumeWhitespace();
87 contents.consumeWhitespace();
88 return contents;
89}
90
91inline bool shouldAcceptUnitlessValue(double value, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk unitless, UnitlessZeroQuirk unitlessZero)
92{
93 // FIXME: Presentational HTML attributes shouldn't use the CSS parser for lengths.
94
95 if (value == 0 && unitlessZero == UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow)
96 return true;
97
98 if (isUnitlessValueParsingEnabledForMode(parserMode))
99 return true;
100
101 return parserMode == HTMLQuirksMode && unitless == UnitlessQuirk::Allow;
102}
103
104static bool canConsumeCalcValue(CalculationCategory category, CSSParserMode parserMode)
105{
106 if (category == CalculationCategory::Length || category == CalculationCategory::Percent || category == CalculationCategory::PercentLength)
107 return true;
108
109 if (parserMode != SVGAttributeMode)
110 return false;
111
112 if (category == CalculationCategory::Number || category == CalculationCategory::PercentNumber)
113 return true;
114
115 return false;
116}
117
118// FIXME: consider pulling in the parsing logic from CSSCalcExpressionNodeParser.
119class CalcParser {
120public:
121 explicit CalcParser(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CalculationCategory destinationCategory, ValueRange valueRange = ValueRange::All, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable = { }, CSSValuePool& pool = CSSValuePool::singleton())
122 : m_sourceRange(range)
123 , m_range(range)
124 , m_pool(pool)
125 {
126 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
127 auto functionId = token.functionId();
128 if (CSSCalcValue::isCalcFunction(functionId))
129 m_calcValue = CSSCalcValue::create(functionId, consumeFunction(m_range), destinationCategory, valueRange, symbolTable);
130 }
131
132 const CSSCalcValue* value() const { return m_calcValue.get(); }
133
134 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeValue()
135 {
136 if (!m_calcValue)
137 return nullptr;
138 m_sourceRange = m_range;
139 return m_pool.createValue(WTFMove(m_calcValue));
140 }
141
142 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeValueIfCategory(CalculationCategory category)
143 {
144 if (!m_calcValue || m_calcValue->category() != category)
145 return nullptr;
146 m_sourceRange = m_range;
147 return m_pool.createValue(WTFMove(m_calcValue));
148 }
149
150 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeInteger(double minimumValue)
151 {
152 if (!m_calcValue)
153 return nullptr;
154 m_sourceRange = m_range;
155 return m_pool.createValue(std::round(std::max(m_calcValue->doubleValue(), minimumValue)), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
156 }
157
158 template<typename IntType> std::optional<IntType> consumeIntegerTypeRaw(double minimumValue)
159 {
160 if (!m_calcValue)
161 return std::nullopt;
162 m_sourceRange = m_range;
163 return clampTo<IntType>(std::round(std::max(m_calcValue->doubleValue(), minimumValue)));
164 }
165
166 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeNumber()
167 {
168 if (!m_calcValue)
169 return nullptr;
170 m_sourceRange = m_range;
171 return m_pool.createValue(m_calcValue->doubleValue(), CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
172 }
173
174 std::optional<double> consumeNumberRaw()
175 {
176 if (!m_calcValue || m_calcValue->category() != CalculationCategory::Number)
177 return std::nullopt;
178 m_sourceRange = m_range;
179 return m_calcValue->doubleValue();
180 }
181
182 std::optional<double> consumePercentRaw()
183 {
184 if (!m_calcValue)
185 return std::nullopt;
186 auto category = m_calcValue->category();
187 if (category != CalculationCategory::Percent)
188 return std::nullopt;
189 m_sourceRange = m_range;
190 return m_calcValue->doubleValue();
191 }
192
193 std::optional<AngleRaw> consumeAngleRaw()
194 {
195 if (!m_calcValue || m_calcValue->category() != CalculationCategory::Angle)
196 return std::nullopt;
197 m_sourceRange = m_range;
198 return { { m_calcValue->primitiveType(), m_calcValue->doubleValue() } };
199 }
200
201 std::optional<LengthRaw> consumeLengthRaw()
202 {
203 if (!m_calcValue || m_calcValue->category() != CalculationCategory::Length)
204 return std::nullopt;
205 m_sourceRange = m_range;
206 return { { m_calcValue->primitiveType(), m_calcValue->doubleValue() } };
207 }
208
209 std::optional<LengthOrPercentRaw> consumeLengthOrPercentRaw()
210 {
211 if (!m_calcValue)
212 return std::nullopt;
213
214 switch (m_calcValue->category()) {
215 case CalculationCategory::Length:
216 m_sourceRange = m_range;
217 return { LengthRaw({ m_calcValue->primitiveType(), m_calcValue->doubleValue() }) };
218 case CalculationCategory::Percent:
219 case CalculationCategory::PercentLength:
220 case CalculationCategory::PercentNumber:
221 m_sourceRange = m_range;
222 return { { m_calcValue->doubleValue() } };
223 default:
224 return std::nullopt;
225 }
226 }
227
228private:
229 CSSParserTokenRange& m_sourceRange;
230 CSSParserTokenRange m_range;
231 RefPtr<CSSCalcValue> m_calcValue;
232 CSSValuePool& m_pool;
233};

237// MARK: Integer (Raw)

239template<typename IntType> static std::optional<IntType> consumeIntegerTypeRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, double minimumValue)
240{
241 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == FunctionToken);
242
243 CalcParser parser(range, CalculationCategory::Number);
244 if (auto calculation = parser.value(); calculation && calculation->category() == CalculationCategory::Number)
245 return parser.consumeIntegerTypeRaw<IntType>(minimumValue);
246
247 return std::nullopt;
248}
249
250template<typename IntType> static std::optional<IntType> consumeIntegerTypeRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, double minimumValue)
251{
252 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
253
254 if (range.peek().numericValueType() == NumberValueType || range.peek().numericValue() < minimumValue)
255 return std::nullopt;
256 return clampTo<IntType>(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue());
257}

259// MARK: Integer (CSSPrimitiveValue - not maintaing calc)
260
261template<typename IntType> static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeIntegerTypeCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, double minimumValue, CSSValuePool& pool)
262{
263 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == FunctionToken);
264
265 if (auto integer = consumeIntegerTypeRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction<IntType>(range, minimumValue))
266 return pool.createValue(*integer, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
267 return nullptr;
268}
269
270template<typename IntType> static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeIntegerTypeCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, double minimumValue, CSSValuePool& pool)
271{
272 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
273
274 if (auto integer = consumeIntegerTypeRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber<IntType>(range, minimumValue))
275 return pool.createValue(*integer, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
276 return nullptr;
277}

281static std::optional<double> validatedNumberRaw(double value, ValueRange valueRange)
282{
283 if (valueRange == ValueRange::NonNegative && value < 0)
284 return std::nullopt;
285 return value;

288static std::optional<double> consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable, ValueRange valueRange)
289{
290 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == FunctionToken);
291
292 CalcParser parser(range, CalculationCategory::Number, valueRange, symbolTable);
293 return parser.consumeNumberRaw();
294}
295
296static std::optional<double> consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange)
297{
298 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
299
300 if (auto validatedValue = validatedNumberRaw(range.peek().numericValue(), valueRange)) {
301 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
302 return validatedValue;
303 }
304 return std::nullopt;
305}
306
307static std::optional<double> consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeIdent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable, ValueRange valueRange)
308{
309 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == IdentToken);
310
311 if (auto variable = symbolTable.get(range.peek().id())) {
312 switch (variable->type) {
313 case CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER:
314 if (auto validatedValue = validatedNumberRaw(variable->value, valueRange)) {
315 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
316 return validatedValue;
317 }
318 break;
319
320 default:
321 break;
322 }
323 }
324 return std::nullopt;
325}

329static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeNumberCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable, ValueRange valueRange, CSSValuePool& pool)
330{
331 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == FunctionToken);
332
333 CalcParser parser(range, CalculationCategory::Number, valueRange, symbolTable, pool);

335}

337static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeNumberCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange, CSSValuePool& pool)
338{
339 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
340
341 auto token = range.peek();
342
343 if (auto validatedValue = validatedNumberRaw(token.numericValue(), valueRange)) {
344 auto unitType = token.unitType();
345 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
346 return pool.createValue(*validatedValue, unitType);
347 }
348 return nullptr;
349}

442
443static std::optional<LengthRaw> consumeLengthRawWithKnownTokenTypeDimension(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk)
444{
445 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == DimensionToken);
446
447 auto& token = range.peek();
448
449 auto unitType = token.unitType();
450 switch (unitType) {
451 case CSSUnitType::CSS_QUIRKY_EMS:
452 if (parserMode != UASheetMode)
453 return std::nullopt;
454 FALLTHROUGH;
455 case CSSUnitType::CSS_EMS:
456 case CSSUnitType::CSS_REMS:
457 case CSSUnitType::CSS_LHS:
458 case CSSUnitType::CSS_RLHS:
459 case CSSUnitType::CSS_CHS:
460 case CSSUnitType::CSS_EXS:
461 case CSSUnitType::CSS_PX:
462 case CSSUnitType::CSS_CM:
463 case CSSUnitType::CSS_MM:
464 case CSSUnitType::CSS_IN:
465 case CSSUnitType::CSS_PT:
466 case CSSUnitType::CSS_PC:
467 case CSSUnitType::CSS_VW:
468 case CSSUnitType::CSS_VH:
469 case CSSUnitType::CSS_VMIN:
470 case CSSUnitType::CSS_VMAX:
471 case CSSUnitType::CSS_Q:
472 break;
473 default:
474 return std::nullopt;
475 }
476
477 if (auto validatedValue = validatedLengthRaw(token.numericValue(), valueRange)) {
478 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
479 return { { unitType, *validatedValue } };
480 }
481 return std::nullopt;
482}
483
484static std::optional<LengthRaw> consumeLengthRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk unitless)
485{
486 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
487
488 auto& token = range.peek();
489
490 if (!shouldAcceptUnitlessValue(token.numericValue(), parserMode, unitless, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow))
491 return std::nullopt;
492
493 if (auto validatedValue = validatedLengthRaw(token.numericValue(), valueRange)) {
494 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
495 return { { CSSUnitType::CSS_PX, *validatedValue } };
496 }
497 return std::nullopt;
498}

538static std::optional<AngleRaw> consumeAngleRawWithKnownTokenTypeDimension(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange, CSSParserMode, UnitlessQuirk, UnitlessZeroQuirk)
539{
540 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == DimensionToken);
541

543 switch (unitType) {
544 case CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG:
545 case CSSUnitType::CSS_RAD:
546 case CSSUnitType::CSS_GRAD:
547 case CSSUnitType::CSS_TURN:
548 return { { unitType, range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue() } };
549 default:
550 break;
551 }
552
553 return std::nullopt;
554}

561 return { { CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG, range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue() } };
562 return std::nullopt;

604static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeTimeCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeDimension(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange, CSSParserMode, UnitlessQuirk, CSSValuePool& pool)
605{
606 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == DimensionToken);
607
608 if (valueRange == ValueRange::NonNegative && range.peek().numericValue() < 0)
609 return nullptr;
610
611 if (auto unit = range.peek().unitType(); unit == CSSUnitType::CSS_MS || unit == CSSUnitType::CSS_S)
612 return pool.createValue(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue(), unit);
613
614 return nullptr;
615}

617static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeTimeCSSPrimitiveValueWithCalcWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable&, ValueRange valueRange, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk unitless, CSSValuePool& pool)
618{
619 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == NumberToken);
620
621 if (unitless == UnitlessQuirk::Allow && shouldAcceptUnitlessValue(range.peek().numericValue(), parserMode, unitless, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow)) {
622 if (valueRange == ValueRange::NonNegative && range.peek().numericValue() < 0)
623 return nullptr;
624 return pool.createValue(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue(), CSSUnitType::CSS_MS);
625 }
626 return nullptr;
627}

629// MARK: Resolution (CSSPrimitiveValue - no calc)
630
631static RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeResolutionCSSPrimitiveValueWithKnownTokenTypeDimension(CSSParserTokenRange& range, AllowXResolutionUnit allowX, CSSValuePool& pool)
632{
633 ASSERT(range.peek().type() == DimensionToken);
634
635 if (auto unit = range.peek().unitType(); unit == CSSUnitType::CSS_DPPX || unit == CSSUnitType::CSS_DPI || unit == CSSUnitType::CSS_DPCM)
636 return pool.createValue(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue(), unit);
637 if (allowX == AllowXResolutionUnit::Allow && range.peek().unitString() == "x")
638 return pool.createValue(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().numericValue(), CSSUnitType::CSS_DPPX);
639
640 return nullptr;
641}

644// MARK: - Primitive value consumers for callers that do NOT know the token type.
645

1072static std::optional<double> consumeAngleRawOrNumberRawAllowingSymbolTableIdent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable, CSSParserMode parserMode)
1073{
1074 auto computeDegrees = [](auto angleRaw) -> std::optional<double> {
1075 if (angleRaw)
1076 return CSSPrimitiveValue::computeDegrees(angleRaw->type, angleRaw->value);
1077 return std::nullopt;
1078 };
1079
1080 auto& token = range.peek();
1081
1082 switch (token.type()) {
1083 case FunctionToken:
1084 if (auto angleRaw = consumeAngleRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(range, symbolTable, ValueRange::All, parserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Forbid))
1085 return computeDegrees(angleRaw);
1086 return consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(range, symbolTable, ValueRange::All);
1087
1088 case DimensionToken:
1089 return computeDegrees(consumeAngleRawWithKnownTokenTypeDimension(range, { }, ValueRange::All, parserMode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Forbid));
1090
1091 case NumberToken:
1092 return consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(range, { }, ValueRange::All);
1093
1094 case IdentToken:
1095 if (auto variable = symbolTable.get(token.id())) {
1096 switch (variable->type) {
1097 case CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG:
1098 case CSSUnitType::CSS_RAD:
1099 case CSSUnitType::CSS_GRAD:
1100 case CSSUnitType::CSS_TURN:
1101 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1102 return CSSPrimitiveValue::computeDegrees(variable->type, variable->value);
1103
1104 case CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER:
1105 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1106 return variable->value;
1107
1108 default:
1109 break;
1110 }
1111 }
1112 break;
1113
1114 default:
1115 break;
1116 }

1118 return std::nullopt;

1159// MARK: - Combination consumers that both allow lookup in the symbol table for IdentTokens and transformations based on result type.
1160
1161template<typename NumberTransformer, typename PercentTransformer>
1162static auto consumeNumberRawOrPercentRawAllowingSymbolTableIdent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable, ValueRange valueRange, NumberTransformer&& numberTranformer, PercentTransformer&& percentTranformer) -> std::optional<decltype(numberTranformer(std::declval<double>()))>
1163{
1164 auto& token = range.peek();
1165
1166 switch (token.type()) {
1167 case FunctionToken: {
1168 if (auto number = consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(range, symbolTable, valueRange))
1169 return numberTranformer(*number);
1170 if (auto percent = consumePercentRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(range, symbolTable, valueRange))
1171 return percentTranformer(*percent);
1172 break;
1173 }
1174
1175 case PercentageToken:
1176 if (auto percent = consumePercentRawWithKnownTokenTypePercentage(range, symbolTable, valueRange))
1177 return percentTranformer(*percent);
1178 break;
1179
1180 case NumberToken:
1181 if (auto number = consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeNumber(range, symbolTable, valueRange))
1182 return numberTranformer(*number);
1183 break;
1184
1185 case IdentToken:
1186 if (auto variable = symbolTable.get(range.peek().id())) {
1187 switch (variable->type) {
1188 case CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE:
1189 if (auto validatedValue = validatedPercentRaw(variable->value, valueRange)) {
1190 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1191 return percentTranformer(*validatedValue);
1192 }
1193 break;
1194
1195 case CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER:
1196 if (auto validatedValue = validatedNumberRaw(variable->value, valueRange)) {
1197 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1198 return numberTranformer(*validatedValue);
1199 }
1200 break;
1201
1202 default:
1203 break;
1204 }
1205 }
1206 break;
1207
1208 default:
1209 break;
1210 }
1211
1212 return std::nullopt;
1213}

1219
1220std::optional<double> consumeFontWeightNumberRaw(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1221{
1222 // Values less than or equal to 0 or greater than or equal to 1000 are parse errors.
1223
1224#if !ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
1225 auto isIntegerAndDivisibleBy100 = [](double value) {
1226 ASSERT(value > 0 && value <= 1000);
1227 return static_cast<int>(value / 100) * 100 == value;
1228 };
1229#endif
1230
1231 auto& token = range.peek();
1232 switch (token.type()) {
1233 case FunctionToken: {
1234 // "[For calc()], the used value resulting from an expression must be clamped to the range allowed in the target context."
1235 auto result = consumeNumberRawWithKnownTokenTypeFunction(range, { }, ValueRange::All);
1236 if (!result)
1237 break;
1238#if !ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
1239 if (!(*result > 0 && *result < 1000) || !isIntegerAndDivisibleBy100(*result))
1240 break;
1241#endif
1242 return std::clamp(*result, std::nextafter(0.0, 1.0), std::nextafter(1000.0, 0.0));
1243 }
1244
1245 case NumberToken: {
1246 auto result = token.numericValue();
1247
1248 // FIXME: This allows value of 1000, unlike the comment above and the behavior of the FunctionToken parsing path.
1249 if (!(result >= 1 && result <= 1000))
1250 break;
1251#if !ENABLE(VARIATION_FONTS)
1252 if (token.numericValueType() != IntegerValueType || !isIntegerAndDivisibleBy100(result))
1253 break;
1254#endif
1255 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1256 return result;
1257 }
1258
1259 default:
1260 break;
1261 }
1262
1263 return std::nullopt;
1264}

1325
1326StringView consumeUrlAsStringView(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1327{
1328 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
1329 if (token.type() == UrlToken) {
1330 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1331 return token.value();
1332 }
1333 if (token.functionId() == CSSValueUrl) {
1334 CSSParserTokenRange urlRange = range;
1335 CSSParserTokenRange urlArgs = urlRange.consumeBlock();
1336 const CSSParserToken& next = urlArgs.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
1337 if (next.type() == BadStringToken || !urlArgs.atEnd())
1338 return StringView();
1339 ASSERT(next.type() == StringToken);
1340 range = urlRange;
1341 range.consumeWhitespace();
1342 return next.value();
1343 }
1344
1345 return { };
1346}
1347
1348RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeUrl(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1349{
1350 StringView url = consumeUrlAsStringView(range);
1351 if (url.isNull())
1352 return nullptr;
1353 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(url.toString(), CSSUnitType::CSS_URI);
1354}
1355
1356static Color consumeOriginColor(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)
1357{
1358 auto value = consumeColor(args, context);
1359 if (!value)
1360 return { };
1361
1362 if (value->isRGBColor())
1363 return value->color();
1364
1365 ASSERT(value->isValueID());
1366 auto keyword = value->valueID();
1367
1368 // FIXME: We don't have enough context in the parser to resolving a system keyword
1369 // correctly. We should package up the relative color parameters and resolve the
1370 // whole thing at the appropriate time when the origin color is a system keyword.
1371 if (StyleColor::isSystemColor(keyword))
1372 return { };
1373
1374 return StyleColor::colorFromKeyword(keyword, { });
1375}

1377static std::optional<double> consumeOptionalAlpha(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
1378{
1379 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range))
1380 return 1.0;
1381
1382 if (auto alphaParameter = consumeNumberRawOrPercentDividedBy100Raw(range))
1383 return std::clamp(*alphaParameter, 0.0, 1.0);
1384
1385 return std::nullopt;
1386}
1387
1388static std::optional<double> consumeOptionalAlphaAllowingSymbolTableIdent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable)
1389{
1390 if (!consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range))
1391 return 1.0;
1392
1393 if (auto alphaParameter = consumeNumberRawOrPercentDividedBy100RawAllowingSymbolTableIdent(range, symbolTable, ValueRange::All))
1394 return std::clamp(*alphaParameter, 0.0, 1.0);
1395
1396 return std::nullopt;
1397}

1399static double normalizeHue(double hue)
1400{
1401 return std::fmod(std::fmod(hue, 360.0) + 360.0, 360.0);
1402}

1404static uint8_t normalizeRGBComponentNumber(double value)
1405{
1406 return convertPrescaledSRGBAFloatToSRGBAByte(value);
1407}
1408
1409static uint8_t normalizeRGBComponentPercentage(double value)
1410{
1411 return convertPrescaledSRGBAFloatToSRGBAByte(value / 100.0 * 255.0);
1412}
1413
1414static std::optional<uint8_t> consumeRelativeRGBComponent(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSCalcSymbolTable& symbolTable)
1415{
1416 return consumeNumberRawOrPercentRawAllowingSymbolTableIdent(range, symbolTable, ValueRange::All, normalizeRGBComponentNumber, normalizeRGBComponentPercentage);
1417}

1419enum class RGBComponentType { Number, Percentage };
1420static uint8_t clampRGBComponent(double value, RGBComponentType componentType)
1421{
1422 switch (componentType) {
1423 case RGBComponentType::Number:
1424 return normalizeRGBComponentNumber(value);
1425 case RGBComponentType::Percentage:
1426 return normalizeRGBComponentPercentage(value);
1427 }
1428
1429 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1430 return 0;
1431}

1433enum class RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax { Commas, WhitespaceSlash };
1434
1435static bool consumeRGBOrHSLSeparator(CSSParserTokenRange& args, RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax syntax)
1436{
1437 if (syntax == RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax::Commas)
1438 return consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args);
1439 return true;
1440}
1441
1442static bool consumeRGBOrHSLAlphaSeparator(CSSParserTokenRange& args, RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax syntax)
1443{
1444 if (syntax == RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax::Commas)
1445 return consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args);
1446 return consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(args);
1447}
1448
1449static std::optional<double> consumeRGBOrHSLOptionalAlpha(CSSParserTokenRange& args, RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax syntax)
1450{
1451 if (!consumeRGBOrHSLAlphaSeparator(args, syntax))
1452 return 1.0;
1453
1454 return consumeNumberRawOrPercentDividedBy100Raw(args);
1455}

1457static Color parseRelativeRGBParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)
1458{
1459 ASSERT(args.peek().id() == CSSValueFrom);
1460 consumeIdentRaw(args);
1461
1462 auto originColor = consumeOriginColor(args, context);
1463 if (!originColor.isValid())
1464 return { };
1465
1466 auto originColorAsSRGB = originColor.toColorTypeLossy<SRGBA<float>>();
1467
1468 CSSCalcSymbolTable symbolTable {
1469 { CSSValueR, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsSRGB.red * 100.0 },
1470 { CSSValueG, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsSRGB.green * 100.0 },
1471 { CSSValueB, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsSRGB.blue * 100.0 },
1472 { CSSValueAlpha, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsSRGB.alpha * 100.0 }
1473 };
1474
1475 auto red = consumeRelativeRGBComponent(args, symbolTable);
1476 if (!red)
1477 return { };
1478
1479 auto green = consumeRelativeRGBComponent(args, symbolTable);
1480 if (!green)
1481 return { };
1482
1483 auto blue = consumeRelativeRGBComponent(args, symbolTable);
1484 if (!blue)
1485 return { };
1486
1487 auto alpha = consumeOptionalAlphaAllowingSymbolTableIdent(args, symbolTable);
1488 if (!alpha)
1489 return { };
1490
1491 if (!args.atEnd())
1492 return { };
1493
1494 auto normalizedAlpha = convertFloatAlphaTo<uint8_t>(*alpha);
1495
1496 return SRGBA<uint8_t> { *red, *green, *blue, normalizedAlpha };
1497}
1498
1499static Color parseNonRelativeRGBParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& args)
1500{
1501 struct InitialComponent {
1502 double value;
1503 RGBComponentType type;
1504 };
1505
1506 auto consumeInitialComponent = [](auto& args) -> std::optional<InitialComponent> {
1507 if (auto number = consumeNumberRaw(args))
1508 return { { *number, RGBComponentType::Number } };
1509 if (auto percent = consumePercentRaw(args))
1510 return { { *percent, RGBComponentType::Percentage } };
1511 return std::nullopt;
1512 };
1513
1514 auto consumeComponent = [](auto& args, auto componentType) {
1515 switch (componentType) {
1516 case RGBComponentType::Percentage:
1517 return consumePercentRaw(args);
1518 case RGBComponentType::Number:
1519 return consumeNumberRaw(args);
1520 }
1521 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1522 };
1523
1524 auto initialComponent = consumeInitialComponent(args);
1525 if (!initialComponent)
1526 return { };
1527
1528 auto componentType = initialComponent->type;
1529 auto red = initialComponent->value;
1530
1531 auto syntax = consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args) ? RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax::Commas : RGBOrHSLSeparatorSyntax::WhitespaceSlash;
1532
1533 auto green = consumeComponent(args, componentType);
1534 if (!green)
1535 return { };
1536
1537 if (!consumeRGBOrHSLSeparator(args, syntax))
1538 return { };
1539
1540 auto blue = consumeComponent(args, componentType);
1541 if (!blue)
1542 return { };
1543
1544 auto alpha = consumeRGBOrHSLOptionalAlpha(args, syntax);
1545 if (!alpha)
1546 return { };
1547
1548 if (!args.atEnd())
1549 return { };
1550
1551 auto normalizedRed = clampRGBComponent(red, componentType);
1552 auto normalizedGreen = clampRGBComponent(*green, componentType);
1553 auto normalizedBlue = clampRGBComponent(*blue, componentType);
1554 auto normalizedAlpha = convertFloatAlphaTo<uint8_t>(*alpha);
1555
1556 return SRGBA<uint8_t> { normalizedRed, normalizedGreen, normalizedBlue, normalizedAlpha };
1557}

1560
1561template<RGBFunctionMode Mode> static Color parseRGBParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
1562{
1563 ASSERT(range.peek().functionId() == (Mode == RGBFunctionMode::RGB ? CSSValueRgb : CSSValueRgba));
1564 auto args = consumeFunction(range);
1565
1566 if constexpr (Mode == RGBFunctionMode::RGB) {
1567 if (context.relativeColorSyntaxEnabled && args.peek().id() == CSSValueFrom)
1568 return parseRelativeRGBParameters(args, context);
1569 }
1570 return parseNonRelativeRGBParameters(args);
1571}

1573static Color colorByNormalizingHSLComponents(double hue, double saturation, double lightness, double alpha)
1574{
1575 auto normalizedHue = normalizeHue(hue);
1576 auto normalizedSaturation = std::clamp(saturation, 0.0, 100.0);
1577 auto normalizedLightness = std::clamp(lightness, 0.0, 100.0);
1578 auto normalizedAlpha = std::clamp(alpha, 0.0, 1.0);
1579
1580 // NOTE: The explicit conversion to SRGBA<uint8_t> is intentional for performance (no extra allocation for
1581 // the extended color) and compatability, forcing serialiazation to use the rgb()/rgba() form.
1582 return convertColor<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(HSLA<float> { static_cast<float>(normalizedHue), static_cast<float>(normalizedSaturation), static_cast<float>(normalizedLightness), static_cast<float>(normalizedAlpha) });
1583}

1585static Color parseRelativeHSLParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)
1586{
1587 ASSERT(args.peek().id() == CSSValueFrom);
1588 consumeIdentRaw(args);
1589
1590 auto originColor = consumeOriginColor(args, context);
1591 if (!originColor.isValid())
1592 return { };
1593
1594 auto originColorAsHSL = originColor.toColorTypeLossy<HSLA<float>>();
1595
1596 CSSCalcSymbolTable symbolTable {
1597 { CSSValueH, CSSUnitType::CSS_DEG, originColorAsHSL.hue },
1598 { CSSValueS, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsHSL.saturation },
1599 { CSSValueL, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsHSL.lightness },
1600 { CSSValueAlpha, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsHSL.alpha * 100.0 }
1601 };
1602
1603 auto hue = consumeAngleRawOrNumberRawAllowingSymbolTableIdent(args, symbolTable, context.mode);
1604 if (!hue)
1605 return { };
1606
1607 auto saturation = consumePercentAllowingSymbolTableIdent(args, symbolTable);
1608 if (!saturation)
1609 return { };
1610

1612 if (!lightness)

1614

1616 if (!alpha)
1617 return { };
1618
1619 if (!args.atEnd())

1622 return colorByNormalizingHSLComponents(*hue, *saturation, *lightness, *alpha);

1669template<typename ComponentType> struct WhitenessBlackness {
1670 ComponentType whiteness;
1671 ComponentType blackness;
1672};
1673
1674template<typename ComponentType> static auto normalizeWhitenessBlackness(ComponentType whiteness, ComponentType blackness) -> WhitenessBlackness<ComponentType>
1675{
1676 // Values outside of these ranges are not invalid, but are clamped to the
1677 // ranges defined here at computed-value time.
1678 WhitenessBlackness<ComponentType> result {
1679 clampTo<ComponentType>(whiteness, 0.0, 100.0),
1680 clampTo<ComponentType>(blackness, 0.0, 100.0)
1681 };
1682
1683 // If the sum of these two arguments is greater than 100%, then at
1684 // computed-value time they are further normalized to add up to 100%, with
1685 // the same relative ratio.
1686 if (auto sum = result.whiteness + result.blackness; sum >= 100) {
1687 result.whiteness *= 100.0 / sum;
1688 result.blackness *= 100.0 / sum;
1689 }
1690
1691 return result;
1692}

1696{

1700

1720 // the extended color) and compatability, forcing serialiazation to use the rgb()/rgba() form.
1721 return convertColor<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(HWBA<float> { static_cast<float>(normalizedHue), static_cast<float>(normalizedWhitness), static_cast<float>(normalizedBlackness), static_cast<float>(*alpha) });
1722}

1926template<typename ColorType, typename ConsumerForRGB, typename ConsumerForAlpha>
1927static Color parseColorFunctionForRGBTypes(CSSParserTokenRange& args, ConsumerForRGB&& rgbConsumer, ConsumerForAlpha&& alphaConsumer)
1928{
1929 double channels[3] = { 0, 0, 0 };
1930 for (auto& channel : channels) {
1931 auto value = rgbConsumer(args);
1932 if (!value)
1933 break;
1934 channel = *value;
1935 }
1936
1937 auto alpha = alphaConsumer(args);
1938 if (!alpha)
1939 return { };
1940
1941 if (!args.atEnd())
1942 return { };
1943
1944 auto normalizedRed = std::clamp(channels[0], 0.0, 1.0);
1945 auto normalizedGreen = std::clamp(channels[1], 0.0, 1.0);
1946 auto normalizedBlue = std::clamp(channels[2], 0.0, 1.0);
1947
1948 return { ColorType { static_cast<float>(normalizedRed), static_cast<float>(normalizedGreen), static_cast<float>(normalizedBlue), static_cast<float>(*alpha) }, Color::Flags::UseColorFunctionSerialization };
1949}
1950
1951template<typename ColorType> static Color parseRelativeColorFunctionForRGBTypes(CSSParserTokenRange& args, Color originColor, const CSSParserContext& context)
1952{
1953 ASSERT(args.peek().id() == CSSValueA98Rgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueDisplayP3 || args.peek().id() == CSSValueProphotoRgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueRec2020 || args.peek().id() == CSSValueSRGB);
1954
1955 // Support sRGB and Display-P3 regardless of the setting as we have shipped support for them for a while.
1956 if (!context.cssColor4 && (args.peek().id() == CSSValueA98Rgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueProphotoRgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueRec2020))
1957 return { };
1958
1959 consumeIdentRaw(args);
1960
1961 auto originColorAsColorType = originColor.toColorTypeLossy<ColorType>();
1962
1963 CSSCalcSymbolTable symbolTable {
1964 { CSSValueR, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsColorType.red * 100.0 },
1965 { CSSValueG, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsColorType.green * 100.0 },
1966 { CSSValueB, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsColorType.blue * 100.0 },
1967 { CSSValueAlpha, CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE, originColorAsColorType.alpha * 100.0 }
1968 };

1976template<typename ColorType> static Color parseColorFunctionForRGBTypes(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)

1981 if (!context.cssColor4 && (args.peek().id() == CSSValueA98Rgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueProphotoRgb || args.peek().id() == CSSValueRec2020))

1992template<typename ConsumerForXYZ, typename ConsumerForAlpha>
1993static Color parseColorFunctionForXYZParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& args, ConsumerForXYZ&& xyzConsumer, ConsumerForAlpha&& alphaConsumer)
1994{

1996 for (auto& channel : channels) {
1997 auto value = xyzConsumer(args);
1998 if (!value)
1999 break;
2000 channel = *value;
2001 }
2002

2004 if (!alpha)
2005 return { };
2006
2007 if (!args.atEnd())
2008 return { };
2009
2010 return { XYZA<float, WhitePoint::D50> { static_cast<float>(channels[0]), static_cast<float>(channels[1]), static_cast<float>(channels[2]), static_cast<float>(*alpha) }, Color::Flags::UseColorFunctionSerialization };
2011}

2120static Color selectFirstColorThatMeetsOrExceedsTargetContrast(const Color& originBackgroundColor, Vector<Color>&& colorsToCompareAgainst, double targetContrast)
2121{
2122 auto originBackgroundColorLuminance = originBackgroundColor.luminance();
2123
2124 for (auto& color : colorsToCompareAgainst) {
2125 if (contrastRatio(originBackgroundColorLuminance, color.luminance()) >= targetContrast)
2126 return WTFMove(color);
2127 }
2128
2129 // If there is a target contrast, and the end of the list is reached without meeting that target,
2130 // either white or black is returned, whichever has the higher contrast.
2131 auto contrastWithWhite = contrastRatio(originBackgroundColorLuminance, 1.0);
2132 auto contrastWithBlack = contrastRatio(originBackgroundColorLuminance, 0.0);
2133 return contrastWithWhite > contrastWithBlack ? Color::white : Color::black;
2134}
2135
2136static Color selectFirstColorWithHighestContrast(const Color& originBackgroundColor, Vector<Color>&& colorsToCompareAgainst)
2137{
2138 auto originBackgroundColorLuminance = originBackgroundColor.luminance();
2139
2140 auto* colorWithGreatestContrast = &colorsToCompareAgainst[0];
2141 double greatestContrastSoFar = 0;
2142 for (auto& color : colorsToCompareAgainst) {
2143 auto contrast = contrastRatio(originBackgroundColorLuminance, color.luminance());
2144 if (contrast > greatestContrastSoFar) {
2145 greatestContrastSoFar = contrast;
2146 colorWithGreatestContrast = &color;
2147 }
2148 }
2149
2150 return WTFMove(*colorWithGreatestContrast);
2151}
2152
2153static Color parseColorContrastFunctionParameters(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2154{
2155 ASSERT(range.peek().functionId() == CSSValueColorContrast);
2156
2157 if (!context.colorContrastEnabled)
2158 return { };
2159
2160 auto args = consumeFunction(range);
2161
2162 auto originBackgroundColor = consumeOriginColor(args, context);
2163 if (!originBackgroundColor.isValid())
2164 return { };
2165
2166 if (!consumeIdentRaw<CSSValueVs>(args))
2167 return { };
2168
2169 Vector<Color> colorsToCompareAgainst;
2170 bool consumedTo = false;
2171 do {
2172 auto colorToCompareAgainst = consumeOriginColor(args, context);
2173 if (!colorToCompareAgainst.isValid())
2174 return { };
2175
2176 colorsToCompareAgainst.append(WTFMove(colorToCompareAgainst));
2177
2178 if (consumeIdentRaw<CSSValueTo>(args)) {
2179 consumedTo = true;
2180 break;
2181 }
2182 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args));
2183
2184 if (colorsToCompareAgainst.size() == 1)
2185 return { };
2186
2187 if (consumedTo) {
2188 auto targetContrast = [&] () -> std::optional<double> {
2189 if (args.peek().type() == IdentToken) {
2190 static constexpr std::pair<CSSValueID, double> targetContrastMappings[] {
2191 { CSSValueAA, 4.5 },
2192 { CSSValueAALarge, 3.0 },
2193 { CSSValueAAA, 7.0 },
2194 { CSSValueAAALarge, 4.5 },
2195 };
2196 static constexpr SortedArrayMap targetContrastMap { targetContrastMappings };
2197 auto value = targetContrastMap.tryGet(args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id());
2198 return value ? std::make_optional(*value) : std::nullopt;
2199 }
2200 return consumeNumberRaw(args);
2201 }();
2202
2203 if (!targetContrast)
2204 return { };
2205
2206 // When a target constast is specified, we select "the first color color to meet or exceed the target contrast."
2207 return selectFirstColorThatMeetsOrExceedsTargetContrast(originBackgroundColor, WTFMove(colorsToCompareAgainst), *targetContrast);
2208 }
2209
2210 // When a target constast is NOT specified, we select "the first color with the highest contrast to the single color."
2211 return selectFirstColorWithHighestContrast(originBackgroundColor, WTFMove(colorsToCompareAgainst));
2212}

2274struct ColorMixPercentages {
2275 double p1;
2276 double p2;
2277};
2278
2279static ColorMixPercentages normalizedMixPercentages(const ColorMixComponent& mixComponents1, const ColorMixComponent& mixComponents2)
2280{
2281 // The percentages are normalized as follows:
2282
2283 // 1. Let p1 be the first percentage and p2 the second one.
2284
2285 // 2. If both percentages are omitted, they each default to 50% (an equal mix of the two colors).
2286 if (!mixComponents1.percentage && !mixComponents2.percentage)
2287 return { 50.0, 50.0 };
2288
2289 ColorMixPercentages result;
2290
2291 if (!mixComponents2.percentage) {
2292 // 3. Otherwise, if p2 is omitted, it becomes 100% - p1
2293 result.p1 = *mixComponents1.percentage;
2294 result.p2 = 100.0 - result.p1;
2295 } else if (!mixComponents1.percentage) {
2296 // 4. Otherwise, if p1 is omitted, it becomes 100% - p2
2297 result.p2 = *mixComponents2.percentage;
2298 result.p1 = 100.0 - result.p2;
2299 } else {
2300 result.p1 = *mixComponents1.percentage;
2301 result.p2 = *mixComponents2.percentage;
2302 }
2303
2304 auto sum = result.p1 + result.p2;
2305
2306 // 5. If the percentages sum to zero do something, tbd. (FIXME: We just use 50 / 50 for this case for now).
2307 if (sum == 0)
2308 return { 50.0, 50.0 };
2309
2310 if (sum != 100.0) {
2311 // 6. Otherwise, if both are provided but do not add up to 100%, they are scaled accordingly so that they
2312 // add up to 100%. This means that p1 becomes p1 / (p1 + p2) and p2 becomes p2 / (p1 + p2).
2313 result.p1 *= 100.0 / sum;
2314 result.p2 *= 100.0 / sum;
2315 }
2316
2317 return result;
2318}

2320// Normalization is special cased for HWBA, which needs to normalize the whiteness and blackness components and convert to sRGB
2321// and HSLA, which just needs to be converted to sRGB. All other color types can go through this non-specialized case.
2322
2323template<typename ColorType> inline Color makeColorTypeByNormalizingComponentsAfterMix(const ColorComponents<float, 4>& colorComponents)
2324{
2325 return makeFromComponents<ColorType>(colorComponents);
2326}
2327
2328template<> inline Color makeColorTypeByNormalizingComponentsAfterMix<HWBA<float>>(const ColorComponents<float, 4>& colorComponents)
2329{
2330 auto [hue, whiteness, blackness, alpha] = colorComponents;
2331 auto [normalizedWhitness, normalizedBlackness] = normalizeWhitenessBlackness(whiteness, blackness);
2332
2333 return convertColor<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(HWBA<float> { hue, normalizedWhitness, normalizedBlackness, alpha });
2334}
2335
2336template<> inline Color makeColorTypeByNormalizingComponentsAfterMix<HSLA<float>>(const ColorComponents<float, 4>& colorComponents)
2337{
2338 return convertColor<SRGBA<uint8_t>>(makeFromComponents<HSLA<float>>(colorComponents));
2339}
2340
2341template<size_t I, typename ComponentType> static void fixupHueComponentsPriorToMix(ColorComponents<ComponentType, 4>& colorComponents1, ColorComponents<ComponentType, 4>& colorComponents2)
2342{
2343 auto normalizeAnglesUsingShorterAlgorithm = [] (auto theta1, auto theta2) -> std::pair<ComponentType, ComponentType> {
2344 // https://drafts.csswg.org/css-color-4/#hue-shorter
2345 auto difference = theta2 - theta1;
2346 if (difference > 180.0)
2347 return { theta1 + 360.0, theta2 };
2348 if (difference < -180.0)
2349 return { theta1, theta2 + 360.0 };
2350 return { theta1, theta2 };
2351 };
2352
2353 // As no other interpolation type was specified, all angles should be normalized to use the "shorter" algorithm.
2354 auto [theta1, theta2] = normalizeAnglesUsingShorterAlgorithm(colorComponents1[I], colorComponents2[I]);
2355 colorComponents1[I] = theta1;
2356 colorComponents2[I] = theta2;
2357}
2358
2359template<typename ColorType> static Color mixColorComponentsInColorSpace(ColorMixPercentages mixPercentages, const Color& color1, const Color& color2)
2360{
2361 auto colorComponents1 = asColorComponents(color1.template toColorTypeLossy<ColorType>());
2362 auto colorComponents2 = asColorComponents(color2.template toColorTypeLossy<ColorType>());
2363
2364 // Perform fixups on any hue/angle components.
2365 constexpr auto componentInfo = ColorType::Model::componentInfo;
2366 if constexpr (componentInfo[0].type == ColorComponentType::Angle)
2367 fixupHueComponentsPriorToMix<0>(colorComponents1, colorComponents2);
2368 if constexpr (componentInfo[1].type == ColorComponentType::Angle)
2369 fixupHueComponentsPriorToMix<1>(colorComponents1, colorComponents2);
2370 if constexpr (componentInfo[2].type == ColorComponentType::Angle)
2371 fixupHueComponentsPriorToMix<2>(colorComponents1, colorComponents2);
2372
2373 auto colorComponentsMixed = mapColorComponents([&] (auto componentFromColor1, auto componentFromColor2) -> float {
2374 return (componentFromColor1 * mixPercentages.p1 / 100.0) + (componentFromColor2 * mixPercentages.p2 / 100.0);
2375 }, colorComponents1, colorComponents2);
2376
2377 return makeColorTypeByNormalizingComponentsAfterMix<ColorType>(colorComponentsMixed);
2378}
2379
2380static Color mixColorComponents(ColorMixColorSpace colorSpace, const ColorMixComponent& mixComponents1, const ColorMixComponent& mixComponents2)
2381{
2382 auto mixPercentages = normalizedMixPercentages(mixComponents1, mixComponents2);
2383
2384 switch (colorSpace) {
2385 case ColorMixColorSpace::Hsl:
2386 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<HSLA<float>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2387 case ColorMixColorSpace::Hwb:
2388 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<HWBA<float>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2389 case ColorMixColorSpace::Lch:
2390 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<LCHA<float>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2391 case ColorMixColorSpace::Lab:
2392 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<Lab<float>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2393 case ColorMixColorSpace::Xyz:
2394 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<XYZA<float, WhitePoint::D50>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2395 case ColorMixColorSpace::Srgb:
2396 return mixColorComponentsInColorSpace<SRGBA<float>>(mixPercentages, mixComponents1.color, mixComponents2.color);
2397 }
2398
2399 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2400}

2435static std::optional<SRGBA<uint8_t>> parseHexColor(CSSParserTokenRange& range, bool acceptQuirkyColors)
2436{
2437 String string;
2438 StringView view;
2439 auto& token = range.peek();
2440 if (token.type() == HashToken)
2441 view = token.value();
2442 else {
2443 if (!acceptQuirkyColors)
2444 return std::nullopt;
2445 if (token.type() == IdentToken) {
2446 view = token.value(); // e.g. FF0000
2447 if (view.length() != 3 && view.length() != 6)
2448 return std::nullopt;
2449 } else if (token.type() == NumberToken || token.type() == DimensionToken) {
2450 if (token.numericValueType() != IntegerValueType)
2451 return std::nullopt;
2452 auto numericValue = token.numericValue();
2453 if (!(numericValue >= 0 && numericValue < 1000000))
2454 return std::nullopt;
2455 auto integerValue = static_cast<int>(token.numericValue());
2456 if (token.type() == NumberToken)
2457 string = String::number(integerValue); // e.g. 112233
2458 else
2459 string = makeString(integerValue, token.unitString()); // e.g. 0001FF
2460 if (string.length() < 6)
2461 string = makeString(&"000000"[string.length()], string);
2462
2463 if (string.length() != 3 && string.length() != 6)
2464 return std::nullopt;
2465 view = string;
2466 } else
2467 return std::nullopt;
2468 }
2469 auto result = CSSParser::parseHexColor(view);
2470 if (!result)
2471 return std::nullopt;
2472 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
2473 return *result;
2474}

2476static Color parseColorFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2477{
2478 CSSParserTokenRange colorRange = range;
2479 CSSValueID functionId = range.peek().functionId();
2480 Color color;
2481 switch (functionId) {
2482 case CSSValueRgb:
2483 color = parseRGBParameters<RGBFunctionMode::RGB>(colorRange, context);
2484 break;
2485 case CSSValueRgba:
2486 color = parseRGBParameters<RGBFunctionMode::RGBA>(colorRange, context);
2487 break;
2488 case CSSValueHsl:
2489 color = parseHSLParameters<HSLFunctionMode::HSL>(colorRange, context);
2490 break;
2491 case CSSValueHsla:
2492 color = parseHSLParameters<HSLFunctionMode::HSLA>(colorRange, context);
2493 break;
2494 case CSSValueHwb:
2495 color = parseHWBParameters(colorRange, context);
2496 break;
2497 case CSSValueLab:
2498 color = parseLabParameters(colorRange, context);
2499 break;
2500 case CSSValueLch:
2501 color = parseLCHParameters(colorRange, context);
2502 break;
2503 case CSSValueColor:
2504 color = parseColorFunctionParameters(colorRange, context);
2505 break;
2506 case CSSValueColorContrast:
2507 color = parseColorContrastFunctionParameters(colorRange, context);
2508 break;
2509 case CSSValueColorMix:
2510 color = parseColorMixFunctionParameters(colorRange, context);
2511 break;
2512 default:
2513 return { };
2514 }
2515 if (color.isValid())
2516 range = colorRange;
2517 return color;
2518}

2520Color consumeColorWorkerSafe(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
2521{
2522 Color result;
2523 auto keyword = range.peek().id();
2524 if (StyleColor::isColorKeyword(keyword)) {
2525 // FIXME: Need a worker-safe way to compute the system colors.
2526 // For now, we detect the system color, but then intentionally fail parsing.
2527 if (StyleColor::isSystemColor(keyword))
2528 return { };
2529 if (!isValueAllowedInMode(keyword, context.mode))

2532 range.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
2533 }
2534

2536 result = *parsedColor;

2538 result = parseColorFunction(range, context);

2547{

2577static bool isVerticalPositionKeywordOnly(const CSSPrimitiveValue& value)
2578{
2579 return value.isValueID() && (value.valueID() == CSSValueTop || value.valueID() == CSSValueBottom);
2580}
2581
2582static PositionCoordinates positionFromOneValue(CSSPrimitiveValue& value)
2583{
2584 bool valueAppliesToYAxisOnly = isVerticalPositionKeywordOnly(value);
2585 if (valueAppliesToYAxisOnly)
2586 return { CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(CSSValueCenter), value };
2587 return { value, CSSPrimitiveValue::createIdentifier(CSSValueCenter) };
2588}
2589
2590static std::optional<PositionCoordinates> positionFromTwoValues(CSSPrimitiveValue& value1, CSSPrimitiveValue& value2)
2591{
2592 bool mustOrderAsXY = isHorizontalPositionKeywordOnly(value1) || isVerticalPositionKeywordOnly(value2) || !value1.isValueID() || !value2.isValueID();
2593 bool mustOrderAsYX = isVerticalPositionKeywordOnly(value1) || isHorizontalPositionKeywordOnly(value2);
2594 if (mustOrderAsXY && mustOrderAsYX)
2595 return std::nullopt;
2596 if (mustOrderAsYX)
2597 return PositionCoordinates { value2, value1 };
2598 return PositionCoordinates { value1, value2 };
2599}

2602template<typename... Args>
2603static Ref<CSSPrimitiveValue> createPrimitiveValuePair(Args&&... args)
2604{
2605 return CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(Pair::create(std::forward<Args>(args)...));

2609// https://drafts.csswg.org/css-backgrounds-3/#propdef-background-position
2610// background-position has special parsing rules, allowing a 3-value syntax:
2611// <bg-position> = [ left | center | right | top | bottom | <length-percentage> ]
2612// |
2613// [ left | center | right | <length-percentage> ]
2614// [ top | center | bottom | <length-percentage> ]
2615// |
2616// [ center | [ left | right ] <length-percentage>? ] &&
2617// [ center | [ top | bottom ] <length-percentage>? ]
2618//
2619static std::optional<PositionCoordinates> backgroundPositionFromThreeValues(const std::array<CSSPrimitiveValue*, 5>& values)
2620{
2621 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> resultX;
2622 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> resultY;
2623
2624 CSSPrimitiveValue* center = nullptr;
2625 for (int i = 0; values[i]; i++) {
2626 CSSPrimitiveValue* currentValue = values[i];
2627 if (!currentValue->isValueID())
2628 return std::nullopt;
2629
2630 CSSValueID id = currentValue->valueID();
2631 if (id == CSSValueCenter) {
2632 if (center)
2633 return std::nullopt;
2634 center = currentValue;
2635 continue;
2636 }
2637
2638 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> result;
2639 if (values[i + 1] && !values[i + 1]->isValueID())
2640 result = CSSPropertyParserHelpersInternal::createPrimitiveValuePair(currentValue, values[++i]);
2641 else
2642 result = currentValue;
2643
2644 if (id == CSSValueLeft || id == CSSValueRight) {
2645 if (resultX)
2646 return std::nullopt;
2647 resultX = result;
2648 } else {
2649 ASSERT(id == CSSValueTop || id == CSSValueBottom);
2650 if (resultY)
2651 return std::nullopt;
2652 resultY = result;
2653 }
2654 }
2655
2656 if (center) {
2657 ASSERT(resultX || resultY);
2658 if (resultX && resultY)
2659 return std::nullopt;
2660 if (!resultX)
2661 resultX = center;
2662 else
2663 resultY = center;
2664 }
2665
2666 ASSERT(resultX && resultY);
2667 return PositionCoordinates { resultX.releaseNonNull(), resultY.releaseNonNull() };
2668}
2669
2670// https://drafts.csswg.org/css-values-4/#typedef-position
2671// <position> = [
2672// [ left | center | right ] || [ top | center | bottom ]
2673// |
2674// [ left | center | right | <length-percentage> ]
2675// [ top | center | bottom | <length-percentage> ]?
2676// |
2677// [ [ left | right ] <length-percentage> ] &&
2678// [ [ top | bottom ] <length-percentage> ]
2679//
2680static std::optional<PositionCoordinates> positionFromFourValues(const std::array<CSSPrimitiveValue*, 5>& values)
2681{
2682 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> resultX;
2683 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> resultY;
2684
2685 for (int i = 0; values[i]; i++) {
2686 CSSPrimitiveValue* currentValue = values[i];
2687 if (!currentValue->isValueID())
2688 return std::nullopt;
2689
2690 CSSValueID id = currentValue->valueID();
2691 if (id == CSSValueCenter)
2692 return std::nullopt;
2693
2694 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> result;
2695 if (values[i + 1] && !values[i + 1]->isValueID())
2696 result = CSSPropertyParserHelpersInternal::createPrimitiveValuePair(currentValue, values[++i]);
2697 else
2698 result = currentValue;
2699
2700 if (id == CSSValueLeft || id == CSSValueRight) {
2701 if (resultX)
2702 return std::nullopt;
2703 resultX = result;
2704 } else {
2705 ASSERT(id == CSSValueTop || id == CSSValueBottom);
2706 if (resultY)
2707 return std::nullopt;
2708 resultY = result;
2709 }
2710 }
2711
2712 ASSERT(resultX && resultY);
2713 return PositionCoordinates { resultX.releaseNonNull(), resultY.releaseNonNull() };
2714}

2716// FIXME: This may consume from the range upon failure. The background
2717// shorthand works around it, but we should just fix it here.
2718std::optional<PositionCoordinates> consumePositionCoordinates(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk unitless, PositionSyntax positionSyntax)
2719{
2720 auto value1 = consumePositionComponent(range, parserMode, unitless);
2721 if (!value1)
2722 return std::nullopt;
2723
2724 auto value2 = consumePositionComponent(range, parserMode, unitless);
2725 if (!value2)
2726 return positionFromOneValue(*value1);
2727
2728 auto value3 = consumePositionComponent(range, parserMode, unitless);
2729 if (!value3)
2730 return positionFromTwoValues(*value1, *value2);
2731
2732 auto value4 = consumePositionComponent(range, parserMode, unitless);
2733
2734 std::array<CSSPrimitiveValue*, 5> values {
2735 value1.get(),
2736 value2.get(),
2737 value3.get(),
2738 value4.get(),
2739 nullptr
2740 };
2741
2742 if (value4)
2743 return positionFromFourValues(values);
2744
2745 if (positionSyntax != PositionSyntax::BackgroundPosition)
2746 return std::nullopt;
2747
2748 return backgroundPositionFromThreeValues(values);
2749}

2758std::optional<PositionCoordinates> consumeOneOrTwoValuedPositionCoordinates(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode parserMode, UnitlessQuirk unitless)

2795static bool consumeDeprecatedGradientColorStop(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSGradientColorStop& stop, const CSSParserContext& context)
2796{
2797 CSSValueID id = range.peek().functionId();
2798 if (id != CSSValueFrom && id != CSSValueTo && id != CSSValueColorStop)
2799 return false;
2800
2801 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(range);
2802 double position;
2803 if (id == CSSValueFrom || id == CSSValueTo) {
2804 position = (id == CSSValueFrom) ? 0 : 1;
2805 } else {
2806 ASSERT(id == CSSValueColorStop);
2807 auto value = consumeNumberRawOrPercentDividedBy100Raw(args);
2808 if (!value)
2809 return false;
2810 position = *value;
2811
2812 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2813 return false;
2814 }
2815
2816 stop.position = CSSValuePool::singleton().createValue(position, CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
2817 stop.color = consumeDeprecatedGradientStopColor(args, context);

2821static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeDeprecatedGradient(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context)
2822{
2823 RefPtr<CSSGradientValue> result;
2824 CSSValueID id = args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
2825 bool isDeprecatedRadialGradient = (id == CSSValueRadial);
2826 if (isDeprecatedRadialGradient)
2827 result = CSSRadialGradientValue::create(NonRepeating, CSSDeprecatedRadialGradient);
2828 else if (id == CSSValueLinear)
2829 result = CSSLinearGradientValue::create(NonRepeating, CSSDeprecatedLinearGradient);
2830 if (!result || !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2831 return nullptr;
2832
2833 auto point = consumeDeprecatedGradientPoint(args, true);
2834 if (!point)
2835 return nullptr;
2836 result->setFirstX(WTFMove(point));
2837 point = consumeDeprecatedGradientPoint(args, false);
2838 if (!point)
2839 return nullptr;
2840 result->setFirstY(WTFMove(point));
2841
2842 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2843 return nullptr;
2844
2845 // For radial gradients only, we now expect a numeric radius.
2846 if (isDeprecatedRadialGradient) {
2847 auto radius = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2848 if (!radius || !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2849 return nullptr;
2850 downcast<CSSRadialGradientValue>(result.get())->setFirstRadius(WTFMove(radius));
2851 }
2852
2853 point = consumeDeprecatedGradientPoint(args, true);
2854 if (!point)
2855 return nullptr;
2856 result->setSecondX(WTFMove(point));
2857 point = consumeDeprecatedGradientPoint(args, false);
2858 if (!point)
2859 return nullptr;
2860 result->setSecondY(WTFMove(point));
2861
2862 // For radial gradients only, we now expect the second radius.
2863 if (isDeprecatedRadialGradient) {
2864 if (!consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2865 return nullptr;
2866 auto radius = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2867 if (!radius)
2868 return nullptr;
2869 downcast<CSSRadialGradientValue>(result.get())->setSecondRadius(WTFMove(radius));
2870 }
2871
2872 CSSGradientColorStop stop;
2873 while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args)) {
2874 if (!consumeDeprecatedGradientColorStop(args, stop, context))
2875 return nullptr;
2876 result->addStop(WTFMove(stop));
2877 }
2878
2879 result->doneAddingStops();
2880 return result;
2881}
2882
2883static bool consumeGradientColorStops(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, CSSGradientValue& gradient)
2884{
2885 bool supportsColorHints = gradient.gradientType() == CSSLinearGradient || gradient.gradientType() == CSSRadialGradient || gradient.gradientType() == CSSConicGradient;
2886
2887 auto consumeStopPosition = [&] {
2888 return gradient.gradientType() == CSSConicGradient
2889 ? consumeAngleOrPercent(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow)
2890 : consumeLengthOrPercent(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
2891 };
2892
2893 // The first color stop cannot be a color hint.
2894 bool previousStopWasColorHint = true;
2895 do {
2896 CSSGradientColorStop stop { consumeColor(range, context), consumeStopPosition(), { } };
2897 if (!stop.color && !stop.position)
2898 return false;
2899
2900 // Two color hints in a row are not allowed.
2901 if (!stop.color && (!supportsColorHints || previousStopWasColorHint))
2902 return false;
2903 previousStopWasColorHint = !stop.color;
2904
2905 // Stops with both a color and a position can have a second position, which shares the same color.
2906 if (stop.color && stop.position) {
2907 if (auto secondPosition = consumeStopPosition()) {
2908 gradient.addStop(CSSGradientColorStop { stop });
2909 stop.position = WTFMove(secondPosition);
2910 }
2911 }
2912 gradient.addStop(WTFMove(stop));
2913 } while (consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(range));
2914
2915 // The last color stop cannot be a color hint.
2916 if (previousStopWasColorHint)
2917 return false;
2918
2919 // Must have two or more stops to be valid.
2920 if (!gradient.hasAtLeastTwoStops())
2921 return false;
2922
2923 gradient.doneAddingStops();
2924 return true;
2925}

2927static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeDeprecatedRadialGradient(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context, CSSGradientRepeat repeating)
2928{
2929 auto result = CSSRadialGradientValue::create(repeating, CSSPrefixedRadialGradient);
2930
2931 auto centerCoordinate = consumeOneOrTwoValuedPositionCoordinates(args, context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid);
2932 if (centerCoordinate && !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
2933 return nullptr;
2934
2935 auto shape = consumeIdent<CSSValueCircle, CSSValueEllipse>(args);
2936 auto sizeKeyword = consumeIdent<CSSValueClosestSide, CSSValueClosestCorner, CSSValueFarthestSide, CSSValueFarthestCorner, CSSValueContain, CSSValueCover>(args);
2937 if (!shape)
2938 shape = consumeIdent<CSSValueCircle, CSSValueEllipse>(args);
2939
2940 // Or, two lengths or percentages
2941 if (!shape && !sizeKeyword) {
2942 auto horizontalSize = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2943 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalSize;
2944 if (horizontalSize) {
2945 verticalSize = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
2946 if (!verticalSize)
2947 return nullptr;
2948 consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args);
2949 result->setEndHorizontalSize(WTFMove(horizontalSize));
2950 result->setEndVerticalSize(WTFMove(verticalSize));
2951 }
2952 } else {
2953 consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args);
2954 }
2955
2956 if (!consumeGradientColorStops(args, context, result))
2957 return nullptr;
2958
2959 if (centerCoordinate) {
2960 result->setFirstX(centerCoordinate->x.copyRef());
2961 result->setFirstY(centerCoordinate->y.copyRef());
2962 result->setSecondX(WTFMove(centerCoordinate->x));
2963 result->setSecondY(WTFMove(centerCoordinate->y));
2964 }
2965 result->setShape(WTFMove(shape));
2966 result->setSizingBehavior(WTFMove(sizeKeyword));
2967
2968 return result;
2969}
2970
2971static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeRadialGradient(CSSParserTokenRange& args, const CSSParserContext& context, CSSGradientRepeat repeating)
2972{
2973 RefPtr<CSSRadialGradientValue> result = CSSRadialGradientValue::create(repeating, CSSRadialGradient);
2974
2975 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> shape;
2976 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> sizeKeyword;
2977 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontalSize;
2978 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalSize;
2979
2980 // First part of grammar, the size/shape clause:
2981 // [ circle || <length> ] |
2982 // [ ellipse || [ <length> | <percentage> ]{2} ] |
2983 // [ [ circle | ellipse] || <size-keyword> ]
2984 for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
2985 if (args.peek().type() == IdentToken) {
2986 CSSValueID id = args.peek().id();
2987 if (id == CSSValueCircle || id == CSSValueEllipse) {
2988 if (shape)
2989 return nullptr;
2990 shape = consumeIdent(args);
2991 } else if (id == CSSValueClosestSide || id == CSSValueClosestCorner || id == CSSValueFarthestSide || id == CSSValueFarthestCorner) {
2992 if (sizeKeyword)
2993 return nullptr;
2994 sizeKeyword = consumeIdent(args);
2995 } else {
2996 break;
2997 }
2998 } else {
2999 auto center = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3000 if (!center)
3001 break;
3002 if (horizontalSize)
3003 return nullptr;
3004 horizontalSize = center;
3005 center = consumeLengthOrPercent(args, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3006 if (center) {
3007 verticalSize = center;
3008 ++i;
3009 }
3010 }
3011 }
3012
3013 // You can specify size as a keyword or a length/percentage, not both.
3014 if (sizeKeyword && horizontalSize)
3015 return nullptr;
3016 // Circles must have 0 or 1 lengths.
3017 if (shape && shape->valueID() == CSSValueCircle && verticalSize)
3018 return nullptr;
3019 // Ellipses must have 0 or 2 length/percentages.
3020 if (shape && shape->valueID() == CSSValueEllipse && horizontalSize && !verticalSize)
3021 return nullptr;
3022 // If there's only one size, it must be a length.
3023 if (!verticalSize && horizontalSize && horizontalSize->isPercentage())
3024 return nullptr;
3025 if ((horizontalSize && horizontalSize->isCalculatedPercentageWithLength())
3026 || (verticalSize && verticalSize->isCalculatedPercentageWithLength()))
3027 return nullptr;
3028
3029 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> centerX;
3030 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> centerY;
3031 if (args.peek().id() == CSSValueAt) {
3032 args.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3033
3034 auto centerCoordinate = consumePositionCoordinates(args, context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, PositionSyntax::Position);
3035 if (!centerCoordinate)
3036 return nullptr;
3037
3038 centerX = WTFMove(centerCoordinate->x);
3039 centerY = WTFMove(centerCoordinate->y);
3040
3041 result->setFirstX(centerX.copyRef());
3042 result->setFirstY(centerY.copyRef());
3043
3044 // Right now, CSS radial gradients have the same start and end centers.
3045 result->setSecondX(centerX.copyRef());
3046 result->setSecondY(centerY.copyRef());
3047 }
3048
3049 if ((shape || sizeKeyword || horizontalSize || centerX || centerY) && !consumeCommaIncludingWhitespace(args))
3050 return nullptr;
3051 if (!consumeGradientColorStops(args, context, *result))
3052 return nullptr;
3053
3054 result->setShape(WTFMove(shape));
3055 result->setSizingBehavior(WTFMove(sizeKeyword));
3056 result->setEndHorizontalSize(WTFMove(horizontalSize));
3057 result->setEndVerticalSize(WTFMove(verticalSize));
3058
3059 return result;
3060}

3203 if (!RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().cssPaintingAPIEnabled())
3204 return nullptr;
3205 if (args.peek().type() != IdentToken)
3206 return nullptr;
3207 auto name = args.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value().toString();
3208
3209 if (!args.atEnd() && args.peek() != CommaToken)
3210 return nullptr;
3211 if (!args.atEnd())
3212 args.consume();
3213
3214 auto argumentList = CSSVariableData::create(args);
3215
3216 while (!args.atEnd())
3217 args.consume();
3218

3223static RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeGeneratedImage(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context)
3224{
3225 CSSValueID id = range.peek().functionId();
3226 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
3227 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(rangeCopy);
3228 RefPtr<CSSValue> result;
3229 if (id == CSSValueRadialGradient)
3230 result = consumeRadialGradient(args, context, NonRepeating);
3231 else if (id == CSSValueRepeatingRadialGradient)
3232 result = consumeRadialGradient(args, context, Repeating);
3233 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitLinearGradient)
3234 result = consumeLinearGradient(args, context, NonRepeating, CSSPrefixedLinearGradient);
3235 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitRepeatingLinearGradient)
3236 result = consumeLinearGradient(args, context, Repeating, CSSPrefixedLinearGradient);
3237 else if (id == CSSValueRepeatingLinearGradient)
3238 result = consumeLinearGradient(args, context, Repeating, CSSLinearGradient);
3239 else if (id == CSSValueLinearGradient)
3240 result = consumeLinearGradient(args, context, NonRepeating, CSSLinearGradient);
3241 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitGradient)
3242 result = consumeDeprecatedGradient(args, context);
3243 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitRadialGradient)
3244 result = consumeDeprecatedRadialGradient(args, context, NonRepeating);
3245 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitRepeatingRadialGradient)
3246 result = consumeDeprecatedRadialGradient(args, context, Repeating);
3247 else if (id == CSSValueConicGradient)
3248 result = consumeConicGradient(args, context, NonRepeating);
3249 else if (id == CSSValueRepeatingConicGradient)
3250 result = consumeConicGradient(args, context, Repeating);
3251 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitCrossFade || id == CSSValueCrossFade)
3252 result = consumeCrossFade(args, context, id == CSSValueWebkitCrossFade);
3253 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitCanvas)
3254 result = consumeWebkitCanvas(args);
3255 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitNamedImage)
3256 result = consumeWebkitNamedImage(args);
3257 else if (id == CSSValueWebkitFilter || id == CSSValueFilter)
3258 result = consumeFilterImage(args, context);
3259#if ENABLE(CSS_PAINTING_API)
3260 else if (id == CSSValuePaint)
3261 result = consumeCustomPaint(args);
3262#endif
3263 if (!result || !args.atEnd())
3264 return nullptr;
3265 range = rangeCopy;
3266 return result;
3267}

3270{

3366static RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> consumeFilterFunction(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, AllowedFilterFunctions allowedFunctions)
3367{
3368 CSSValueID filterType = range.peek().functionId();
3369 switch (allowedFunctions) {
3370 case AllowedFilterFunctions::PixelFilters:
3371 if (!isPixelFilterFunction(filterType))
3372 return nullptr;
3373 break;
3374 case AllowedFilterFunctions::ColorFilters:
3375 if (!isColorFilterFunction(filterType))
3376 return nullptr;
3377 break;
3378 }
3379
3380 CSSParserTokenRange args = consumeFunction(range);
3381 RefPtr<CSSFunctionValue> filterValue = CSSFunctionValue::create(filterType);
3382
3383 if (filterType == CSSValueAppleInvertLightness) {
3384 if (!args.atEnd())
3385 return nullptr;
3386 return filterValue;
3387 }
3388
3389 RefPtr<CSSValue> parsedValue;
3390
3391 if (filterType == CSSValueDropShadow)
3392 parsedValue = consumeSingleShadow(args, context, false, false);
3393 else {
3394 if (args.atEnd())
3395 return filterValue;
3396
3397 if (filterType == CSSValueHueRotate)
3398 parsedValue = consumeAngle(args, context.mode, UnitlessQuirk::Forbid, UnitlessZeroQuirk::Allow);
3399 else if (filterType == CSSValueBlur)
3400 parsedValue = consumeLength(args, HTMLStandardMode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3401 else {
3402 parsedValue = consumePercent(args, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3403 if (!parsedValue)
3404 parsedValue = consumeNumber(args, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3405 if (parsedValue && !allowsValuesGreaterThanOne(filterType)) {
3406 bool isPercentage = downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*parsedValue).isPercentage();
3407 double maxAllowed = isPercentage ? 100.0 : 1.0;
3408 if (downcast<CSSPrimitiveValue>(*parsedValue).doubleValue() > maxAllowed)
3409 parsedValue = CSSPrimitiveValue::create(maxAllowed, isPercentage ? CSSUnitType::CSS_PERCENTAGE : CSSUnitType::CSS_NUMBER);
3410 }
3411 }
3412 }
3413 if (!parsedValue || !args.atEnd())
3414 return nullptr;
3415 filterValue->append(parsedValue.releaseNonNull());
3416 return filterValue;
3417}

3419RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeFilter(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, AllowedFilterFunctions allowedFunctions)
3420{
3421 if (range.peek().id() == CSSValueNone)
3422 return consumeIdent(range);
3423
3424 bool referenceFiltersAllowed = allowedFunctions == AllowedFilterFunctions::PixelFilters;
3425 auto list = CSSValueList::createSpaceSeparated();
3426 do {
3427 RefPtr<CSSValue> filterValue = referenceFiltersAllowed ? consumeUrl(range) : nullptr;
3428 if (!filterValue) {
3429 filterValue = consumeFilterFunction(range, context, allowedFunctions);
3430 if (!filterValue)
3431 return nullptr;
3432 }
3433 list->append(filterValue.releaseNonNull());
3434 } while (!range.atEnd());
3435
3436 return list.ptr();
3437}

3439RefPtr<CSSShadowValue> consumeSingleShadow(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, bool allowInset, bool allowSpread)
3440{
3441 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> style;
3442 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> color;
3443 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> horizontalOffset;
3444 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> verticalOffset;
3445 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> blurRadius;
3446 RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> spreadDistance;
3447
3448 for (size_t i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
3449 if (range.atEnd())
3450 break;
3451
3452 const CSSParserToken& nextToken = range.peek();
3453 // If we have come to a comma (e.g. if this range represents a comma-separated list of <shadow>s), we are done parsing this <shadow>.
3454 if (nextToken.type() == CommaToken)
3455 break;
3456
3457 if (nextToken.id() == CSSValueInset) {
3458 if (!allowInset || style)
3459 return nullptr;
3460 style = consumeIdent(range);
3461 continue;
3462 }
3463
3464 auto maybeColor = consumeColor(range, context);
3465 if (maybeColor) {
3466 // If we just parsed a color but already had one, the given token range is not a valid <shadow>.
3467 if (color)
3468 return nullptr;
3469 color = maybeColor;
3470 continue;
3471 }
3472
3473 // If the current token is neither a color nor the `inset` keyword, it must be the lengths component of this value.
3474 if (horizontalOffset || verticalOffset || blurRadius || spreadDistance) {
3475 // If we've already parsed these lengths, the given value is invalid as there cannot be two lengths components in a single <shadow> value.
3476 return nullptr;
3477 }
3478 horizontalOffset = consumeLength(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
3479 if (!horizontalOffset)
3480 return nullptr;
3481 verticalOffset = consumeLength(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
3482 if (!verticalOffset)
3483 return nullptr;
3484
3485 const CSSParserToken& token = range.peek();
3486 // The explicit check for calc() is unfortunate. This is ensuring that we only fail parsing if there is a length, but it fails the range check.
3487 if (token.type() == DimensionToken || token.type() == NumberToken || (token.type() == FunctionToken && CSSCalcValue::isCalcFunction(token.functionId()))) {
3488 blurRadius = consumeLength(range, context.mode, ValueRange::NonNegative);
3489 if (!blurRadius)
3490 return nullptr;
3491 }
3492
3493 if (blurRadius && allowSpread)
3494 spreadDistance = consumeLength(range, context.mode, ValueRange::All);
3495 }
3496
3497 // In order for this to be a valid <shadow>, at least these lengths must be present.
3498 if (!horizontalOffset || !verticalOffset)
3499 return nullptr;
3500 return CSSShadowValue::create(WTFMove(horizontalOffset), WTFMove(verticalOffset), WTFMove(blurRadius), WTFMove(spreadDistance), WTFMove(style), WTFMove(color));
3501}

3503RefPtr<CSSValue> consumeImage(CSSParserTokenRange& range, const CSSParserContext& context, OptionSet<AllowedImageType> allowedImageTypes)
3504{
3505 if (range.peek().type() == StringToken && allowedImageTypes.contains(AllowedImageType::RawStringAsURL)) {
3506 return CSSImageValue::create(context.completeURL(range.consumeIncludingWhitespace().value().toAtomString().string()),
3507 context.isContentOpaque ? LoadedFromOpaqueSource::Yes : LoadedFromOpaqueSource::No);
3508 }
3509
3510 if (range.peek().type() == FunctionToken) {
3511 CSSValueID functionId = range.peek().functionId();
3512 if ((allowedImageTypes.contains(AllowedImageType::GeneratedImage)) && isGeneratedImage(functionId))
3513 return consumeGeneratedImage(range, context);
3514
3515 if (allowedImageTypes.contains(AllowedImageType::ImageSet)) {
3516 if (functionId == CSSValueImageSet)
3517 return consumeImageSet(range, context, (allowedImageTypes | AllowedImageType::RawStringAsURL) - AllowedImageType::ImageSet);
3518 if (functionId == CSSValueWebkitImageSet)
3519 return consumeImageSet(range, context, AllowedImageType::URLFunction);
3520 }
3521 }
3522
3523 if (allowedImageTypes.contains(AllowedImageType::URLFunction)) {
3524 if (auto string = consumeUrlAsStringView(range); !string.isNull()) {
3525 return CSSImageValue::create(context.completeURL(string.toAtomString().string()),
3526 context.isContentOpaque ? LoadedFromOpaqueSource::Yes : LoadedFromOpaqueSource::No);
3527 }
3528 }
3529
3530 return nullptr;
3531}

3539// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#typedef-counter-style-name
3540RefPtr<CSSPrimitiveValue> consumeCounterStyleName(CSSParserTokenRange& range)
3541{
3542 // <counter-style-name> is a <custom-ident> that is not an ASCII case-insensitive match for "none".
3543 auto valueID = range.peek().id();
3544 if (valueID == CSSValueNone)
3545 return nullptr;
3546 // If the value is an ASCII case-insensitive match for any of the predefined counter styles, lowercase it.
3547 if (auto name = consumeCustomIdent(range, isPredefinedCounterStyle(valueID)))
3548 return name;
3549 return nullptr;
3550}

3552// https://www.w3.org/TR/css-counter-styles-3/#typedef-counter-style-name
3553AtomString consumeCounterStyleNameInPrelude(CSSParserTokenRange& prelude)
3554{
3555 auto nameToken = prelude.consumeIncludingWhitespace();
3556 if (!prelude.atEnd())
3557 return AtomString();
3558 // Ensure this token is a valid <custom-ident>.
3559 if (nameToken.type() != IdentToken || isCSSWideKeyword(nameToken.id()))
3560 return AtomString();
3561 // In the context of the prelude of an @counter-style rule, a <counter-style-name> must not be an ASCII
3562 // case-insensitive match for "decimal" or "disc". No <counter-style-name>, prelude or not, may be an ASCII
3563 // case-insensitive match for "none".
3564 if (identMatches<CSSValueDecimal, CSSValueDisc, CSSValueNone>(nameToken.id()))
3565 return AtomString();
3566 auto name = nameToken.value();
3567 return isPredefinedCounterStyle(nameToken.id()) ? name.convertToASCIILowercaseAtom() : name.toAtomString();
3568}

3702std::optional<FontRaw> consumeFontRaw(CSSParserTokenRange& range, CSSParserMode parserMode)
3703{
3704 // Let's check if there is an inherit or initial somewhere in the shorthand.
3705 CSSParserTokenRange rangeCopy = range;
3706 while (!rangeCopy.atEnd()) {
3707 CSSValueID id = rangeCopy.consumeIncludingWhitespace().id();
3708 if (id == CSSValueInherit || id == CSSValueInitial)
3709 return std::nullopt;
3710 }
3711
3712 FontRaw result;
3713
3714 while (!range.atEnd()) {
3715 CSSValueID id = range.peek().id();
3716 if (!result.style) {
3717 if ((result.style = consumeFontStyleRaw(range, parserMode)))
3718 continue;
3719 }
3720 if (!result.variantCaps && (id == CSSValueNormal || id == CSSValueSmallCaps)) {
3721 // Font variant in the shorthand is particular, it only accepts normal or small-caps.
3722 // See https://drafts.csswg.org/css-fonts/#propdef-font
3723 if ((result.variantCaps = consumeFontVariantCSS21Raw(range)))
3724 continue;
3725 }
3726 if (!result.weight) {
3727 if ((result.weight = consumeFontWeightRaw(range)))
3728 continue;
3729 }
3730 if (!result.stretch) {
3731 if ((result.stretch = consumeFontStretchKeywordValueRaw(range)))
3732 continue;
3733 }
3734 break;
3735 }
3736
3737 if (range.atEnd())
3738 return std::nullopt;
3739
3740 // Now a font size _must_ come.
3741 if (auto size = consumeFontSizeRaw(range, parserMode))
3742 result.size = *size;
3743 else
3744 return std::nullopt;
3745
3746 if (range.atEnd())
3747 return std::nullopt;
3748
3749 if (consumeSlashIncludingWhitespace(range)) {
3750 if (!(result.lineHeight = consumeLineHeightRaw(range, parserMode)))
3751 return std::nullopt;
3752 }
3753
3754 // Font family must come now.
3755 if (auto family = consumeFontFamilyRaw(range))
3756 result.family = *family;
3757 else
3758 return std::nullopt;
3759
3760 if (!range.atEnd())
3761 return std::nullopt;
3762
3763 return result;
3764}
